# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Joe,
Whose disco moves stole every show.
    His platforms were high,
    He'd reach for the sky,
While the spinning ball cast its bright glow.

The DJ would spin funky tracks,
As dancers showed off their slick acts.
    The bass would thump loud,
    Exciting the crowd,
With polyester suits and cool macks.

Those nights in the seventies shine,
With memories that taste sweet as wine.
    Though disco may fade,
    The mark it has made,
Lives on in our hearts for all time.

